&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>Tutorial at ISMIR 2022: Trustworthy MIR: Creating MIR applications with values</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220625_ismir2022_tutorial/</link><pubDate>Sat, 25 Jun 2022 02:00:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220625_ismir2022_tutorial/</guid><description>&lt;p>I am happy to announce that I will hold a tutorial at &lt;a href="https://ismir2022.ismir.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ISMIR 2022&lt;/a> on &lt;a href="https://chbeu.github.io/talks/tu02_ismir2022_trustworthy_mir/">Trustworthy MIR: Creating MIR applications with values&lt;/a> together with &lt;a href="https://andrebola.github.io/about/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Andrés Ferraro&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://emiliagomez.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Emilia Gómez&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="https://lorenzoporcaro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lorenzo Porcaro&lt;/a>. The goal of the tutorial is to show how values, such as fairness and diversity, can be embedded in the life cycle of MIR systems to make them trustworthy: from algorithmic design to evaluation practices and regulatory proposals. To achieve that, we will discuss examples of, among the others, popularity bias, gender bias, algorithmic bias, music styles underrepresentation, and diversity-related phenomena (e.g. filter bubbles).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Naturally, I hope that you can learn a lot from the tutorial. As a very positive side effect, I am looking forward to collaborating with &lt;a href="https://andrebola.github.io/about/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Andrés Ferraro&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://emiliagomez.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Emilia Gómez&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="https://lorenzoporcaro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lorenzo Porcaro&lt;/a> on this topic. For sure, we will have a blast.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Featured on UU's website for research on Equality, Diversity &amp; Inclusion</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2021-07-02-featured-on-uu-s-website/</link><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jul 2021 12:42:01 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2021-07-02-featured-on-uu-s-website/</guid><description>&lt;p>What an honor that my recent work with &lt;a href="https://andrebola.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Andrés Ferraro&lt;/a> is featured as an example for research on Equality, Diversity &amp;amp; Inclusion at Utrecht University&amp;rsquo;s website. There is also a sneak peek to an upcoming work with &lt;a href="https://jcdevaney.tumblr.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Johanna Devaney&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Read the &lt;a href="https://www.uu.nl/en/organisation/equality-diversity-inclusion/music-recommenders-show-a-strong-gender-bias" target="_blank" rel="noopener">article based the interview with me&lt;/a>.
